<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="851" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d851">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">836.48 1930 Hurricane/41: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-10">September 10, 1930</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>49. Major Watson proceeding on destroyer <hi rend="italic">Gilmer</hi>,
                            which left Hampton Roads this morning. He will probably arrive at Santo
                            Domingo September 12. He is being designated as Naval Attaché with a
                            view to his assignment as Food Administrator, as requested by the
                            Dominican Republic. Further formal instructions follow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
